name: Bounce Teochew Fishball Noodles - Northshore Plaza II

reviews.text:
Ordered the fish ball noodles dry , sauce mix was on point and tasty. Fishballs cooked al dente , not overcooked. BOUNCY FISHBALLS.

Worth a try, one of the better fishball noodles in the area.

The Indian or foreigner who took my order really kayu minded the on menu show kway Tiao fish ball soup $5.50 is not those "budget meal" but I order mi tai mak soup n the guy say I need to top up 50¢ just to change the kway Tiao to mi tai mak n that cost me $6.30 plus the container. The portion that he give me is super small. Frankly speaking I won't buy if I'm the one eating the food! Make no sense by changing the type or noodle plus only with soup want me additional 50¢ if I change to mee pok or mee Kia I nothing to say cos got add egg to make those noodles correct! The worst thing is when I get home i got scolded by my wife why I so stupid to pay such price for just 5 fishball+ noodle + soup. Shld have buy dry mee pok with the same with 5 fishball+ soup+ chilli+ mincemeat n additional container. Don't feel eating this stall in future.
Tried the dry minced meat fishball noodle. The taste is alright, noodle had the springy texture. Fishballs are ok but can be better. Friendly service. Overall a pleasant experience.

Tried the dry noodles twice already it’s yummy! But soup not so nice.
Extra star as Abang who served me was chirpy and polite! Thanks!
Stand at counter for 10mins and dont even want to take my order. Act busy with delivery order but never prioritise dine in customer. act like nobody standing at counter.
